body:
Consider the following system of ODEs,
\begin{equation}
\begin{cases}
x'=-x^2-xy+x\\
y'=-y^2-xy+y
\end{cases}
\end{equation}
with initial conditions $x(0)=x_0>0$ and $y(0)=y_0>0$. I should prove that $(x(t),y(t))$ is defined for all $t\geq 0$ and that $x(t)>0$ and $y(t)>0$ for all $t\geq 0$. Any suggestion?
